1
00:00:25,625 --> 00:00:26,458
[YUKIKAZE CM 1A]
Entering orbit,

2
00:00:26,541 --> 00:00:29,083
200 megameters from Pluto.

3
00:00:29,166 --> 00:00:31,000
--Battle stations!
--[alarm blares]

4
00:00:31,083 --> 00:00:32,250
[YUKIKAZE CM 1B]
Enemy sightings

5
00:00:32,333 --> 00:00:33,875
are negative, sir.

6
00:00:33,958 --> 00:00:36,916
Seas are calm today.
It's kind of eerie.

7
00:00:37,000 --> 00:00:39,125
Send up a signal round--
Do it now.

8
00:00:44,541 --> 00:00:45,500
[KIRISHIMA CM 1A]
Signal round sighted

9
00:00:45,583 --> 00:00:47,208
from vanguard ship <i>Yukikaze</i> .

10
00:00:47,291 --> 00:00:49,291
Message: We have
entered operation area.

11
00:00:49,375 --> 00:00:51,000
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B] Spotters
report enemy sighted, sir.

12
00:00:51,083 --> 00:00:54,291
Multiple contacts.
Starboard, four o'clock.

13
00:00:54,375 --> 00:00:57,875
EM Wave blackout cleared.
Identify those vessels.

14
00:00:57,958 --> 00:00:59,583
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B] One
Super-Dreadnaught Class Warship,

15
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:03,750
7 battleships, 22 cruisers,
70 destroyers and counting, sir.

16
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,583
All ships to combat positions.

17
00:01:05,666 --> 00:01:08,416
Thirty degrees starboard.
Ready the torpedoes.

18
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,375
[KIRISHIMA CM 1C]
Turning starboard.

19
00:01:10,458 --> 00:01:13,958
[alarm blaring]

20
00:01:34,458 --> 00:01:36,583
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B]
Distance: 7.5 megameters.

21
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:38,458
Incoming message
from the enemy.

22
00:01:38,541 --> 00:01:42,416
"Attention all Earth vessels.
Surrender or be destroyed."

23
00:01:42,500 --> 00:01:44,166
How should we respond, sir?

24
00:01:44,250 --> 00:01:46,500
[OKITA]
Tell them, "Nuts."

25
00:01:46,583 --> 00:01:47,500
[KIRISHIMA CM 1A]
Sir?

26
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:49,291
Go on. Send it.

27
00:01:49,375 --> 00:01:53,458
Aye-aye. Earth fleet
responding: "Nuts!"

28
00:02:06,416 --> 00:02:07,833
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D]
The Yuguri is destroyed!

29
00:02:07,916 --> 00:02:09,208
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B]
The Kurama is leaving formation.

30
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:11,583
--Now, sir?
--Not yet.

31
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:16,041
Enemy ship is
within firing range.

32
00:02:16,125 --> 00:02:18,250
Target locked.

33
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:21,291
Open up all the gun ports--fire!

34
00:02:36,958 --> 00:02:42,291
[MALE ABUKUMA OFFICER 1A]
Evasive maneuver!

35
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:44,333
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D] Two more
of our cruisers are down!

36
00:02:44,416 --> 00:02:46,541
[OKITA] Still no word
from the Amaterasu?

37
00:02:46,625 --> 00:02:48,041
[KIRISHIMA CM 1A]
No message received, sir.

38
00:02:48,125 --> 00:02:49,208
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B] Another
Space Cruiser has been hit...

39
00:02:49,291 --> 00:02:50,750
You really believe
they'll come, Admiral?

40
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:52,458
We have to believe.

41
00:02:57,708 --> 00:02:59,416
--[KIRISHIMA CM 1F gasps]
--[OKITA] Uh!

42
00:03:03,375 --> 00:03:04,208
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D]
Damage report:

43
00:03:04,291 --> 00:03:05,791
we're leaking cyanide gas.

44
00:03:05,875 --> 00:03:07,250
[KIRISHIMA CM 1E] Engine
output dropping!

45
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:10,125
Damage control. Get those
bulkheads down, now!

46
00:03:10,208 --> 00:03:11,708
[alarm blaring]

47
00:03:11,791 --> 00:03:13,375
[KIRISHIMA CM 1G, 1H yell]

48
00:03:15,125 --> 00:03:16,333
Hang on, kid,
do you hear me!

49
00:03:16,416 --> 00:03:18,125
Don't you dare die on me!

50
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:21,958
[gasps]
Mom. Mom, is that you?

51
00:03:22,041 --> 00:03:23,208
Damn it!

52
00:03:23,291 --> 00:03:24,458
[FLEET CAPTAIN 1A]
We've lost control.

53
00:03:24,541 --> 00:03:26,000
We're leaving formation!

54
00:03:26,083 --> 00:03:27,541
[FLEET CAPTAIN 1B] Our main
cannon isn't powerful enough!

55
00:03:27,625 --> 00:03:29,791
The enemy's advantage
is overwhelming, sir.

56
00:03:29,875 --> 00:03:31,791
[MAMORU KODAI]
This was an ambush?

57
00:03:31,875 --> 00:03:33,708
Turn the ship, reverse course!

58
00:03:41,166 --> 00:03:42,500
[KIRISHIMA CM 1K]
Fire team, where are you?

59
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:45,208
Keep working! We can't
lose any more output.

60
00:03:45,291 --> 00:03:47,333
And keep an eye out
for those plasma leaks!

61
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:50,833
[YABU] Chief. We've got things
stabilized for now.

62
00:03:50,916 --> 00:03:52,541
But if we keep
taking these hits...

63
00:03:52,625 --> 00:03:54,250
[TOKUGAWA]
I told you, we'll be fine.

64
00:03:54,333 --> 00:03:55,666
Have faith.

65
00:03:55,750 --> 00:03:58,666
The Admiral's at the helm.
He'll get us through this.

66
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,833
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B]
Eighty percent of our fleet

67
00:03:59,916 --> 00:04:01,583
is out of commission, sir.

68
00:04:01,666 --> 00:04:02,916
[OKITA]
Mmm.

69
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,666
[KIRISHIMA CM 1M]
Signal from Amaterasu confirmed!

70
00:04:04,750 --> 00:04:06,791
They're on course
at interstellar speed.

71
00:04:06,875 --> 00:04:09,083
They'll be passing
Neptune shortly, sir!

72
00:04:11,083 --> 00:04:12,291
[KIRISHIMA CM 1M]
Package will reach Mars

73
00:04:12,375 --> 00:04:14,250
in 10 minutes, sir!

74
00:04:14,333 --> 00:04:16,458
Send encrypted message to HQ.

75
00:04:16,541 --> 00:04:19,333
"The Stone Door
of Heaven is open."

76
00:04:21,916 --> 00:04:23,791
[MALE HQ CM 1A]
Battle report: at 1200,

77
00:04:23,875 --> 00:04:27,458
the First Fleet engaged the
enemy 380 megameters from Pluto.

78
00:04:27,541 --> 00:04:29,958
State of combat
currently unknown.

79
00:04:30,041 --> 00:04:33,041
Message received from
Admiral Okita on the <i>Kirishima</i> .

80
00:04:33,125 --> 00:04:35,875
"The Stone Door
of Heaven is open."

81
00:04:35,958 --> 00:04:38,333
[TODO] Then so far,
everything is going as planned.

82
00:04:38,416 --> 00:04:40,458
When is the rendezvous
with the package?

83
00:04:40,541 --> 00:04:41,916
There's a two-man
recovery squad,

84
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,208
waiting at the old Arcadia Port.

85
00:04:55,500 --> 00:04:58,500
[SHIMA] Today makes 3 weeks
since we were dropped here.

86
00:04:58,583 --> 00:05:00,750
You think Operation M
is going our way?

87
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:02,291
Beats the hell out of me.

88
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:04,791
All I know is my brother's
fighting at Pluto.

89
00:05:04,875 --> 00:05:06,583
While I'm staring at red dirt.

90
00:05:06,666 --> 00:05:08,541
[radio beeping]

91
00:05:08,625 --> 00:05:10,083
Yeah?

92
00:05:10,166 --> 00:05:11,541
Roger that.

93
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:15,875
That ends the staring.

94
00:05:26,083 --> 00:05:27,500
That's it?

95
00:05:31,541 --> 00:05:33,125
[KODAI, SHIMA gasp]

96
00:05:35,541 --> 00:05:36,666
Hey, where you going?

97
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:38,625
There's an escape pod.

98
00:05:41,750 --> 00:05:47,166
[footsteps]

99
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:49,666
[KODAI gasps]
That's it.

100
00:06:01,625 --> 00:06:03,250
Well?

101
00:06:06,291 --> 00:06:08,916
[SHIMA]
She's who we're here to meet?

102
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:12,958
[KODAI] Don't know.
She sure is beautiful.

103
00:06:17,583 --> 00:06:18,958
[SHIMA gasps]

104
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:23,791
[SHIMA]
This must be it.

105
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:28,333
[FLEET CM 1A]
The Isokaze's gone!

106
00:06:28,416 --> 00:06:29,958
[FLEET CAPTAIN 1C]
Keep fighting! Fire!

107
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:51,750
The recovery team has confirmed
package in hand, sir.

108
00:06:51,833 --> 00:06:55,041
Mm. Then the First Fleet's
operation is complete.

109
00:06:55,125 --> 00:06:57,166
Turn this ship around.
Full retreat.

110
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:58,541
--Huh?
--[beeping]

111
00:06:58,625 --> 00:07:00,500
Enemy destroyer approaching
quickly from above, sir!

112
00:07:00,583 --> 00:07:01,750
[YUKIKAZE CM 1D]
Target sighted!

113
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:03,208
[KIRISHIMA CM 1M]
They're trying to lock on!

114
00:07:12,375 --> 00:07:14,458
Tubes one and two, fire!

115
00:07:17,916 --> 00:07:19,125
[YUKIKAZE CM 1D]
Confirmed hit, target destroyed!

116
00:07:19,208 --> 00:07:20,916
Gotcha!

117
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:23,375
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D]
Enemy destroyer is down, sir.

118
00:07:23,458 --> 00:07:25,250
They're reorganizing
their fleet.

119
00:07:25,333 --> 00:07:27,083
Order remaining vessels
to retreat.

120
00:07:27,166 --> 00:07:28,041
[KIRISHIMA CM 1A]
Sending order now, sir!

121
00:07:28,125 --> 00:07:29,458
[OKITA]
How many of us survived?

122
00:07:29,541 --> 00:07:30,916
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D]
Just us and one other ship.

123
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:32,083
That assault destroyer.

124
00:07:32,166 --> 00:07:33,583
[OKITA]
Who is she?

125
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:36,000
[KIRISHIMA CM 1D]
Captain Kodai's <i>Yukikaze</i> .

126
00:07:37,375 --> 00:07:38,250
[YUKIKAZE CM 1E]
Incoming retreat order

127
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:39,541
from the <i>Kirishima</i> .

128
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,000
Retreat?

129
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:44,125
[YUKIKAZE CM 1E] Message:
"Disengage and withdraw.

130
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:45,541
Follow us home."

131
00:07:45,625 --> 00:07:46,833
[KIRISHIMA CM 1C]
Exiting battlefield.

132
00:07:46,916 --> 00:07:48,625
Turning hard to starboard.

133
00:07:57,583 --> 00:07:59,791
They ignored us!
They're not turning!

134
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:01,958
They're what?

135
00:08:02,041 --> 00:08:04,541
Kodai. Follow my lead!

136
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,958
Negative, sir.
We're not going anywhere.

137
00:08:07,041 --> 00:08:08,416
[OKITA]
That's an order!

138
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,458
The <i>Yukikaze</i> will stay
on the battlefield.

139
00:08:10,541 --> 00:08:12,416
We'll support
the <i>Kirishima</i> 's withdrawal.

140
00:08:12,500 --> 00:08:14,791
Don't do this! We've made
great sacrifices

141
00:08:14,875 --> 00:08:18,791
but the operation was a success!
Now let's go home!

142
00:08:18,875 --> 00:08:20,250
[MAMORU KODAI]
If we don't play this right,

143
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:21,916
our whole fleet
will be wiped out!

144
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:23,208
And with no one left
to protect Earth

145
00:08:23,291 --> 00:08:25,000
there won't be a home
to go back to!

146
00:08:25,083 --> 00:08:26,250
[OKITA]
Kodai!

147
00:08:26,333 --> 00:08:28,625
Listen, Admiral.
You can't die here.

148
00:08:28,708 --> 00:08:30,083
You have to escape!

149
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:33,500
Earth needs you. You may be
the best chance we've got.

150
00:08:33,583 --> 00:08:35,750
[OKITA]
I could say the same about you.

151
00:08:35,833 --> 00:08:37,708
We need you, Captain!

152
00:08:37,791 --> 00:08:39,500
Thank you for
saying that, sir.

153
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:41,791
I'm going to take
those words to the grave.

154
00:08:41,875 --> 00:08:44,125
[OKITA] No, stop!
You don't understand!

155
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:47,166
Give 'em hell. I'm leaving
the earth in your care.

156
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:50,000
[OKITA]
Kodai!

157
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:54,916
Well, all right.
Let's take it to 'em.

158
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,958
Ha. We're only
outnumbered 50 to 1.

159
00:08:58,041 --> 00:09:00,125
[MAMORU KODAI]
Mm.

160
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:02,791
♪ Crossing the waves
drifting out ♪

161
00:09:02,875 --> 00:09:04,625
♪ on the galactic sea, ♪

162
00:09:04,708 --> 00:09:09,416
♪ fixing our sights
on Alpha Centauri! ♪

163
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,750
[YUKIKAZE CMs]
♪ Bright be the fiery glow, ♪

164
00:09:11,833 --> 00:09:14,250
♪ of the stars celestial. ♪

165
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:18,250
♪ Lighting the way
ahead to capture destiny! ♪

166
00:09:18,333 --> 00:09:19,750
[YUKIKAZE CM, FIRST MATE]
♪ Set sail! ♪

167
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,375
♪ We're leaving shore! ♪

168
00:09:22,458 --> 00:09:25,875
♪ Raise the anchor!
Home no more! ♪

169
00:09:25,958 --> 00:09:29,458
♪ Hold steady, crewman brother.
Onward past Mars! ♪

170
00:09:29,541 --> 00:09:31,791
I'm sorry everyone.

171
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:34,625
[YUKIKAZE CMs continue singing]

172
00:09:34,708 --> 00:09:35,875
[KIRISHIMA CM 1C]
They're flying directly

173
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:38,083
into the enemy fleet.

174
00:09:38,166 --> 00:09:39,791
Admiral?

175
00:09:39,875 --> 00:09:44,500
[OKITA] Maintain course.
Full speed ahead.

176
00:09:44,583 --> 00:09:47,083
Maintain course, full speed!

177
00:09:47,166 --> 00:09:50,500
[OKITA]
Stay alive, Kodai. Stay alive.

178
00:09:50,583 --> 00:10:00,541
♪

179
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:32,500
[KODAI] This is the Uzume,
requesting permission to dock.

180
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:36,541
What's going on?

181
00:10:36,625 --> 00:10:39,041
Where's my brother,
and the rest of the fleet?

182
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:58,458
[HIRATA] Package secured.
Well done, soldiers.

183
00:10:58,541 --> 00:11:00,750
[KODAI]
Hirata. We're in the dark here.

184
00:11:00,833 --> 00:11:02,125
What happened?

185
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:04,583
Where's my brother's ship,
is he okay?

186
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:11,125
[GUY ON SHIP] Our flagship
has secured the capsule

187
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:13,625
from the Amaterasu,
and set a course for Earth.

188
00:11:13,708 --> 00:11:15,833
It cost many lives
and many ships.

189
00:11:15,916 --> 00:11:18,750
But the main objective of
Operation M has been achieved.

190
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:21,000
That means the path is clear
for the Yamato Plan.

191
00:11:21,083 --> 00:11:22,333
The gambit worked.

192
00:11:22,416 --> 00:11:24,750
[HIJIKATA]
No. This is just the start.

193
00:11:24,833 --> 00:11:26,791
There's too much we don't
know about our enemy,

194
00:11:26,875 --> 00:11:28,750
and how they'll counter.

195
00:11:28,833 --> 00:11:32,041
All we can say for sure
is they're monsters.

196
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:35,291
Demons who call
themselves Gamilans.

197
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:37,458
Beyond that, we're in the dark.

198
00:11:53,750 --> 00:11:56,208
[KIRISHIMA CM 1C]
Now entering Earth's orbit.

199
00:11:56,291 --> 00:11:57,416
[KIRISHIMA CM 1B]
Two planet bombs sighted,

200
00:11:57,500 --> 00:11:59,833
type MN3. Passing on
the starboard side,

201
00:11:59,916 --> 00:12:01,958
on a collision course
with Earth.

202
00:12:07,291 --> 00:12:10,666
Passing satellite orbit.
Speed is unchanged.

203
00:12:10,750 --> 00:12:15,041
[OKITA] Firing's pointless.
Just a waste of rounds.

204
00:12:15,125 --> 00:12:17,541
We don't have the power
to stop them.

205
00:12:17,625 --> 00:12:27,541
♪

206
00:12:27,625 --> 00:12:29,000
[OKITA]
Hard to believe this ugly,

207
00:12:29,083 --> 00:12:31,750
red rock is Mother Earth.

208
00:12:33,916 --> 00:12:35,625
Just you wait, devils.

209
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:38,208
I'll fight you
all the way to the end.

210
00:12:38,291 --> 00:12:41,791
I'll never despair.
I won't give you that.

211
00:12:41,875 --> 00:12:46,875
Even if I'm the last one
breathing, I'll never despair.

212
00:12:46,958 --> 00:12:51,833
♪

213
00:12:51,916 --> 00:12:54,916
[MORI]
The year is 2199 A.D.

214
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:57,916
The human race is on
the verge of extinction.

215
00:12:58,000 --> 00:13:00,875
Our planet as we know it
nearly destroyed.

216
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:04,541
Eight years ago, Earth made
first contact with alien life.

217
00:13:04,625 --> 00:13:07,291
The celebrations
did not last long.

218
00:13:07,375 --> 00:13:09,791
Attempts at peace
were quickly met with war,

219
00:13:09,875 --> 00:13:12,875
and merciless,
indiscriminate attacks.

220
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:15,666
The scale of devastation and
the power of their weaponry

221
00:13:15,750 --> 00:13:18,416
was beyond anything
we'd ever seen.

222
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:39,291
At the second battle of Mars,
we won a Pyrrhic victory,

223
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:44,416
managing to narrowly
fend off their direct assault.

224
00:13:44,500 --> 00:13:47,208
But then, they shifted
their strategy,

225
00:13:47,291 --> 00:13:50,958
relying on an onslaught
of long-range planet bombs.

226
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:52,625
With no way
to defend the surface,

227
00:13:52,708 --> 00:13:55,166
humankind was
forced underground.

228
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:59,500
We built underground cities and
retreated into the darkness.

229
00:14:02,708 --> 00:14:05,500
We devoted our greatest
minds and resources into

230
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:08,250
the Earth Defense Fleet,
only to see it almost

231
00:14:08,333 --> 00:14:11,291
completely wiped out
by the enemy.

232
00:14:11,375 --> 00:14:13,958
Their planet bombs
have dried up the land,

233
00:14:14,041 --> 00:14:15,666
polluted the atmosphere,

234
00:14:15,750 --> 00:14:19,166
and eradicated
all life on the surface.

235
00:14:21,166 --> 00:14:24,250
And still the cruel shadow
of death is growing,

236
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,875
spreading downward
to our underground cities,

237
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:29,666
the last fortress of humankind.

238
00:14:30,958 --> 00:14:35,250
The facts are inescapable.
We are headed toward our end.

239
00:14:38,208 --> 00:14:40,291
Our scientists estimate
that the human race

240
00:14:40,375 --> 00:14:43,208
could be extinct within a year.

241
00:14:43,291 --> 00:14:46,583
The enemy has re-engineered
the environment of Pluto.

242
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:48,916
And continues to launch
their horrific weapons

243
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:51,250
from a base there.

244
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:55,083
So do we know why the aliens
are doing this to our planet?

245
00:14:55,166 --> 00:14:57,250
We don't know.

246
00:14:57,333 --> 00:15:00,750
But we have theories.
Just as we terraformed Mars,

247
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:05,250
they may be terraforming Earth,
so that they can live here.

248
00:15:07,666 --> 00:15:10,500
[NANBU] Must be tough teaching
kids on top of your HQ job.

249
00:15:10,583 --> 00:15:12,750
I mean, what do you say?

250
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:14,666
Jeez, another riot?

251
00:15:14,750 --> 00:15:16,958
The unrest is inevitable now.

252
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:20,583
All hail the ice queen,
unemotional as ever.

253
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:24,541
[NANBU] Lots of gossip
flying around lately.

254
00:15:24,625 --> 00:15:26,000
People are saying
the only survivors

255
00:15:26,083 --> 00:15:28,458
from the First Fleet
were on the <i>Kirishima</i> .

256
00:15:28,541 --> 00:15:29,833
That's right.

257
00:15:29,916 --> 00:15:32,333
That's not all. Rumor is
the whole thing was a ruse.

258
00:15:32,416 --> 00:15:34,208
Sounds crazy,
but they say Operation M

259
00:15:34,291 --> 00:15:36,416
was just a diversion
for the enemy.

260
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:37,875
And the real
mission's classified

261
00:15:37,958 --> 00:15:39,291
so only the top brass knew,

262
00:15:39,375 --> 00:15:43,083
leaving everyone else
to go blind to the slaughter.

263
00:15:43,166 --> 00:15:45,166
[KODAI]
Hey. You!

264
00:15:45,250 --> 00:15:47,416
That talk about a diversion,
is that true?

265
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:49,666
[NANBU] I don't know.
It's just something I heard.

266
00:15:49,750 --> 00:15:51,083
How should I know?

267
00:15:51,166 --> 00:15:53,250
Well, you guys work
at Headquarters, right?

268
00:15:53,333 --> 00:15:55,500
Where's Commander Okita,
is he here?

269
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:04,166
[MORI]
Hey! What's your name, pilot?

270
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:05,500
You're way out of line!

271
00:16:05,583 --> 00:16:06,958
Oh, well, uh.

272
00:16:07,041 --> 00:16:09,541
Cut him some slack, ma'am.
We're back from battle.

273
00:16:09,625 --> 00:16:11,250
[MORI]
The Vice-Admiral's in the ward

274
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,791
recovering from his injuries.

275
00:16:13,875 --> 00:16:14,958
Lieutenant, let's go.

276
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:16,666
Uh, yes, ma'am.

277
00:16:20,583 --> 00:16:22,833
[SHIMA] That's a trip.
She looks just like her.

278
00:16:22,916 --> 00:16:24,708
You're imagining things.

279
00:16:24,791 --> 00:16:26,333
Where do you think
you're going?

280
00:16:26,416 --> 00:16:27,958
[KODAI]
The hospital zone.

281
00:16:30,791 --> 00:16:32,666
[SHIMA] You're seriously
gonna talk to him?

282
00:16:32,750 --> 00:16:35,000
We're supposed to be
on standby, you know.

283
00:16:35,083 --> 00:16:37,208
I need to hear it
straight from him.

284
00:16:44,166 --> 00:16:47,250
Uncanny. Sometimes
I think you're immortal.

285
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,708
No, Dr. Sado, I just
have the best physician

286
00:16:49,791 --> 00:16:51,333
in the fleet treating me.

287
00:16:51,416 --> 00:16:53,000
[DR. SADO]
Don't flatter me, I am not!

288
00:16:53,083 --> 00:16:54,500
Heh. Well, maybe.

289
00:16:54,583 --> 00:16:55,958
Where do they have the capsule?

290
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,875
[HIJIKATA] Tech team's
looking at it now.

291
00:16:57,958 --> 00:17:00,750
They should be done
analyzing it soon.

292
00:17:00,833 --> 00:17:02,125
[door hisses, scrapes]

293
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:03,833
[HARADA]
Hey, this is a private room.

294
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:05,250
You can't just come in!

295
00:17:05,333 --> 00:17:07,000
Back off, I need to
talk to the Admiral!

296
00:17:07,083 --> 00:17:08,125
But sir, you--!

297
00:17:08,208 --> 00:17:09,916
Is it true Operation M
was nothing more

298
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,500
than a damn diversion?

299
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:14,166
Did my brother and everyone else
know what they were flying into?

300
00:17:14,250 --> 00:17:16,750
[HIJIKATA]
Shut up, soldier!

301
00:17:16,833 --> 00:17:18,750
[KODAI]
Admiral Hijikata!

302
00:17:18,833 --> 00:17:20,541
[SHIMA groans]

303
00:17:20,625 --> 00:17:24,125
I'm sorry. That's Susumu Kodai,
a former student of mine.

304
00:17:24,208 --> 00:17:28,041
[OKITA] Kodai. Then you
must be Mamoru Kodai's...

305
00:17:28,125 --> 00:17:30,875
That's right, Captain Kodai
of the <i>Yukikaze</i> .

306
00:17:30,958 --> 00:17:33,208
He was my brother.

307
00:17:33,291 --> 00:17:38,083
Mamoru Kodai was a great man.
One of the best to ever serve.

308
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,666
He bravely sacrificed
everything for the cause.

309
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:44,000
And I'm the one
who led him to his death.

310
00:17:44,083 --> 00:17:45,708
I'm sorry.

311
00:17:53,291 --> 00:17:54,750
[SHIMA]
So now what?

312
00:17:54,833 --> 00:17:56,750
[KODAI] We follow orders
and go back to standby.

313
00:17:56,833 --> 00:17:58,333
What else?

314
00:17:58,416 --> 00:17:59,500
[SHIMA]
Works for me.

315
00:17:59,583 --> 00:18:01,416
[DR. SADO]
Hey!

316
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,541
[KODAI gasps]
Sorry, Doctor.

317
00:18:03,625 --> 00:18:05,083
I meant no disrespect.

318
00:18:05,166 --> 00:18:07,375
I get it,
emotions are running high.

319
00:18:07,458 --> 00:18:09,250
But you're sure as hell
not the only one here

320
00:18:09,333 --> 00:18:11,916
to lose friends and family
in this war, kid.

321
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,666
Just try to remember that.

322
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:18,041
I just can't believe we got to
see Admiral Hijikata in person.

323
00:18:18,125 --> 00:18:19,541
Those two have been
good friends since

324
00:18:19,625 --> 00:18:22,208
they were young recruits
in Officer Training.

325
00:18:22,291 --> 00:18:25,583
Just like you two right now,
from the looks of it.

326
00:18:25,666 --> 00:18:27,791
Give me a break,
we're nothing like them.

327
00:18:27,875 --> 00:18:29,250
I guess time will tell.

328
00:18:29,333 --> 00:18:31,375
But more importantly,
who wants a drink?

329
00:18:31,458 --> 00:18:32,500
Doctor!

330
00:18:32,583 --> 00:18:34,791
This isn't that
jet fuel hooch, either!

331
00:18:34,875 --> 00:18:37,291
This is real saké--
it's hard to find!

332
00:18:37,375 --> 00:18:40,708
[giggles]
Nice try. But they're gone, sir.

333
00:18:41,958 --> 00:18:44,041
Their loss.

334
00:18:44,125 --> 00:18:46,875
[phone beeping]

335
00:18:46,958 --> 00:18:47,958
[phone handset clicks]

336
00:18:48,041 --> 00:18:49,458
[OKITA]
Go ahead.

337
00:18:49,541 --> 00:18:51,708
[FEMALE HQ CM 1A] Test
preparations are ready, sir.

338
00:18:51,791 --> 00:18:54,291
On my way.

339
00:18:54,375 --> 00:18:55,750
[phone handset clicks]

340
00:18:56,750 --> 00:18:59,791
[HIJIKATA] Seems our faith
was well-placed.

341
00:18:59,875 --> 00:19:02,958
At least so far, she's delivered
on everything she said.

342
00:19:05,541 --> 00:19:08,333
It's been a year since we
switched from the Izumo Plan.

343
00:19:08,416 --> 00:19:11,333
And now the Yamato Plan
is finally bearing fruit.

344
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:12,791
What about the crew?

345
00:19:12,875 --> 00:19:14,666
They're on standby
according to plan.

346
00:19:14,750 --> 00:19:15,750
We can activate them...

347
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:17,666
It's a damn shame about Kodai.

348
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:19,208
[TODO]
Very good.

349
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:21,541
[MALE DECK CM 1A]
All right, team, let's move!

350
00:19:21,625 --> 00:19:23,625
[KODAI] I've never seen
a ship like this.

351
00:19:23,708 --> 00:19:26,416
Me neither. You think it's
an air defense prototype?

352
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,875
[KATO] Type-Zero
Space Model 52.

353
00:19:28,958 --> 00:19:30,750
Cosmo Zero for short.

354
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:33,125
She's a ship-based fighter
meant for space deployment,

355
00:19:33,208 --> 00:19:36,125
not for air defense.
You sightseeing?

356
00:19:36,208 --> 00:19:38,500
We were ordered to
report here for standby.

357
00:19:38,583 --> 00:19:40,958
[KATO]
Is that right? Same as me.

358
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:42,083
[MALE DECK CM 1B]
Lieutenant Kato!

359
00:19:42,166 --> 00:19:44,000
Yeah! Be right there.

360
00:19:44,083 --> 00:19:46,083
Don't touch her.

361
00:19:48,375 --> 00:19:49,708
Lieutenant Kato?

362
00:19:49,791 --> 00:19:52,458
Saburo Kato,
the best ace in the fleet.

363
00:19:52,541 --> 00:19:53,750
Yeah?

364
00:19:53,833 --> 00:19:56,500
[KODAI]
Funny, isn't it?

365
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:59,125
When someone says
not to do something...

366
00:19:59,208 --> 00:20:00,583
Can't resist.

367
00:20:00,666 --> 00:20:02,458
[alarm blarring]

368
00:20:02,541 --> 00:20:04,125
[MALE HQ CM 1B] Enemy mobile
squadron has broken through

369
00:20:04,208 --> 00:20:06,041
our defenses, entering
atmosphere now.

370
00:20:06,125 --> 00:20:07,416
[MALE HQ CM 1D] Alarms sounded
in fighter hanger.

371
00:20:07,500 --> 00:20:09,125
Prepare to engage! Code Red!

372
00:20:09,208 --> 00:20:10,750
I guess they noticed.

373
00:20:10,833 --> 00:20:12,291
[FEMALE HQ CM 1B]
Enemy approaching dry sea zone

374
00:20:12,375 --> 00:20:14,250
off Cape Bonomisaki.
Estimated target...

375
00:20:14,333 --> 00:20:15,666
Well, that was good timing.

376
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:18,041
Yeah, we can use this beauty
to shoot 'em down.

377
00:20:18,125 --> 00:20:20,875
[KATO] We don't have time
to wait for orders, just do it!

378
00:20:23,458 --> 00:20:25,208
[KATO]
Hey, what are you doing?

379
00:20:25,291 --> 00:20:27,041
That's <i>my</i> fighter!

380
00:20:27,125 --> 00:20:29,791
Hold on, you idiots!
Get back here!

381
00:20:31,708 --> 00:20:36,708
♪

382
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:42,041
[KODAI]
Closing in.

383
00:20:42,125 --> 00:20:45,208
Up there! Looks like
a recon plane.

384
00:20:45,291 --> 00:20:46,208
Can ya' do this?

385
00:20:46,291 --> 00:20:48,958
Oh, yeah.
This is for my brother.

386
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:04,375
[KODAI]
You're mine.

387
00:21:06,208 --> 00:21:07,541
[BOTH gasp]

388
00:21:07,625 --> 00:21:09,791
[SHIMA] The deck crew must
have unloaded the weapons!

389
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,833
[beeping]

390
00:21:15,083 --> 00:21:17,208
Ah! Damn it!

391
00:21:17,291 --> 00:21:18,708
[KODAI grunts]

392
00:21:20,583 --> 00:21:23,541
[KODAI]
A system error! Hang on!

393
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:34,791
[KODAI grunting]
You okay?

394
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:37,625
[SHIMA]
Yeah. I guess.

395
00:21:37,708 --> 00:21:39,916
But in these lightweight suits
we may not last long enough

396
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:42,416
for an extraction team
to get here.

397
00:21:43,458 --> 00:21:46,083
Kodai! Where are you going?

398
00:21:53,458 --> 00:21:55,125
[SHIMA]
You see something?

399
00:22:02,083 --> 00:22:05,041
--[SHIMA] What is that?
--[KODAI] Not sure.

400
00:22:05,125 --> 00:22:08,500
[KODAI] You think that's
what they were looking for?

401
00:22:08,583 --> 00:22:11,458
[SHIMA] Can't be. It's just
a sunken battleship.

402
00:22:11,541 --> 00:22:14,333
Must be over 200 years old!

403
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:16,083
[KODAI]
Yeah.

404
00:24:12,791 --> 00:24:15,000
[OKITA]
The year is 2199.

405
00:24:15,083 --> 00:24:17,416
Earth is on the verge
of destruction.

406
00:24:17,500 --> 00:24:20,125
And now, humanity's
last hope slips past

407
00:24:20,208 --> 00:24:23,333
the outstretched claws of
the enemy and takes flight.

408
00:24:23,416 --> 00:24:26,958
The name of this hope:
Space Battleship <i>Yamato</i> .

409
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:29,416
Its crew will leave
our home world behind

410
00:24:29,500 --> 00:24:32,416
and set a course
for unexplored space.

411
00:24:32,500 --> 00:24:35,750
Next time:
"Toward a Sea of Stars."

412
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:38,333
There are 365 days left

413
00:24:38,416 --> 00:24:41,208
before the extinction
of the human race.

